Computing Bayes Factors for two binomial models

log_BF = function(Y,
                  theta_0 = 0.5,
                  n = 20,
                  a = 1,
                  b = 1) {
  lBF = lgamma(a + b) + lgamma(a + Y) + lgamma(b + n - Y)
  lBF = lBF - (lgamma(a) + lgamma(b) + lgamma(n + a + b) + Y * log(theta_0) +
                 (n - Y) * log(1 - theta_0))
  return(lBF)
}
plot_BF = function(n, a, b) {
  Y = seq(0, 20, by = 1)
  plot(
    Y,
    log_BF(Y, n = n, a = a, b = b) / log(10),
    type = "b",
    ylab = "Bayes Factor",
    xlab = "Y",
    ylim = c(-4, 5),
    axes = FALSE,
    main = paste(" a =", a, " b =", b)
  )
  axis(1)
  axis(2,
       at = seq(-3, 4, by = 1),
       labels = 10 ^ seq(-3, 4, by = 1))
  abline(h = c(2, 3), lty = 2)
  box()
}
par(mfcol = c(1, 2))
plot_BF(n = 20, a = 1, b = 1)
plot_BF(n = 20, a = 0.5, b = 0.5)

par(mfcol = c(1, 2))
plot_BF(n = 20, a = 50, b = 50)
plot_BF(n = 20, a = 50, b = 1)

Model selection for Bayesian regression model. First we will simulate some data.

simulate_data = function(n) {
  X = seq(-1, 1, length = n)
  true_mu = X + 0.05 * log(abs(X))
  Y = rnorm(n, true_mu , 0.1)
  JAGS = list(Y = Y, X = X, n = n)
  return(list(JAGS = JAGS, true_mu = true_mu))
}

Let’s plot this.

dat = simulate_data(n = 100)
par(mfcol = c(1, 1))
plot(dat$JAGS$X, dat$JAGS$Y, type = "p")

Bayesian model averaging. Let’s start with a model.

JAGS_BMA = function() {
  # Likelihood
  for (i in 1:n) {
    Y[i]  ~ dnorm(mu[i], inv_var)
    mu[i] <- beta[1] + beta[2] * X[i] + beta[3] * X[i] * X[i]
  }
  
  #Priors
  beta[1] ~ dnorm(0, 0.1)
  beta[2] ~ dnorm(0, 0.1)
  alpha   ~ dnorm(0, 0.1)
  delta   ~ dbern(0.5)
  beta[3] <- delta * alpha
  inv_var ~ dgamma(0.01, 0.01)
}

And then fit it to our synthetic data.

fit_JAGS_BMA = jags(
  data = dat$JAGS,
  parameters.to.save = c("beta", "delta", "mu"),
  n.chains = 1,
  n.iter = 10000,
  n.burnin = 1000,
  model.file = JAGS_BMA
)

JAGS_Quad = function() {
  # Likelihood
  for (i in 1:n) {
    Y[i]  ~ dnorm(mu[i], inv_var)
    mu[i] <- beta[1] + beta[2] * X[i] + beta[3] * X[i] * X[i]
  }
  
  #Priors
  beta[1] ~ dnorm(0, 0.1)
  beta[2] ~ dnorm(0, 0.1)
  beta[3] ~ dnorm(0, 0.1)
  
  inv_var ~ dgamma(0.01, 0.01)
}

And again fit it to our synthetic data.

JAGS_Linear = function() {
  # Likelihood
  for (i in 1:n) {
    Y[i]  ~ dnorm(mu[i], inv_var)
    mu[i] <- beta[1] + beta[2] * X[i]
  }
  
  #Priors
  beta[1] ~ dnorm(0, 0.1)
  beta[2] ~ dnorm(0, 0.1)
  
  inv_var ~ dgamma(0.01, 0.01)
}

  model.file = JAGS_Linear
)

Posterior predictive checks

compute_Bayes_p_value = function(Y_pred_mad, Y) {
  d_pred_max = apply(Y_pred_mat, 1, max)
  d_pred_min = apply(Y_pred_mat, 1, min)
  d_pred_mean = apply(Y_pred_mat, 1, mean)
  d_pred_sd = apply(Y_pred_mat, 1, sd)
  d_pred_span = d_pred_max - d_pred_min
  
  d_max = max(Y)
  d_min = min(Y)
  d_span = d_max - d_min
  d_mean = mean(Y)
  d_sd = sd(Y)
  
  Bayes_p_value = list()
  Bayes_p_value$d_max = mean(d_pred_max > d_max)
  Bayes_p_value$d_min = mean(d_pred_min > d_min)
  Bayes_p_value$d_span = mean(d_pred_span > d_span)
  Bayes_p_value$d_sd = mean(d_pred_sd > d_sd)
  Bayes_p_value$d_mean = mean(d_pred_mean > d_mean)
  
  
  return(list(
    Bayes_p_value = as.data.frame(Bayes_p_value),
    d_stats = list(
      d_max = d_max,
      d_min = d_min,
      d_span = d_span,
      d_sd = d_sd,
      d_mean = d_mean,
      d_pred_max = d_pred_max,
      d_pred_min = d_pred_min,
      d_pred_mean = d_pred_mean,
      d_pred_span = d_pred_span,
      d_pred_sd = d_pred_sd
    )
  ))
}
simulate_data_linear = function(n) {
  X = seq(-1, 1, length = n)
  true_mu = X
  Y = rnorm(n, true_mu , 1)
  JAGS = list(Y = Y, X = X, n = n)
  return(list(JAGS = JAGS, true_mu = true_mu))
}

simulate_data_quad = function(n) {
  X = seq(-1, 1, length = n)
  true_mu = X + 5 * X ^ 2
  Y = rnorm(n, true_mu , 1)
  JAGS = list(Y = Y, X = X, n = n)
  return(list(JAGS = JAGS, true_mu = true_mu))
}


n = 1000
dat_linear = simulate_data_linear(n)
dat_quad = simulate_data_quad(n)

JAGS_BMA_pred = function() {
  # Likelihood
  for (i in 1:n) {
    Y[i]  ~ dnorm(mu[i], inv_var)
    mu[i] <- beta[1] + beta[2] * X[i] + beta[3] * X[i] * X[i]
  }
  #prediction
  for (i in 1:n_pred) {
    Y_pred[i]  ~ dnorm(mu_pred[i], inv_var)
    mu_pred[i] <-
      beta[1] + beta[2] * X_pred[i] + beta[3] * X_pred[i] * X_pred[i]
  }
  #Priors
  beta[1] ~ dnorm(0, 0.1)
  beta[2] ~ dnorm(0, 0.1)
  alpha   ~ dnorm(0, 0.1)
  delta   ~ dbern(0.5)
  beta[3] <- delta * alpha
  inv_var ~ dgamma(0.01, 0.01)
}

fit_JAGS = jags(
  data = list(
    Y = dat_linear$JAGS$Y,
    X = dat_linear$JAGS$X,
    X_pred = dat_linear$JAGS$X,
    n = n,
    n_pred = n
  ),
  parameters.to.save = c("Y_pred"),
  n.chains = 1,
  n.iter = 10000,
  n.burnin = 1000,
  model.file = JAGS_BMA_pred
)
plot_pred_checks = function(pred_checks,lwd=1.5){
  d_stats = pred_checks$d_stats
  par(mfcol=c(3,2))
  hist(d_stats$d_pred_max,xlab="d_max",
       main=paste("d_max p-value =",pred_checks$Bayes_p_value["d_max"]),
       xlim = range(c(d_stats$d_pred_max,d_stats$d_max)))
  abline(v=d_stats$d_max,col="red",lwd=lwd)
  hist(d_stats$d_pred_min,xlab="d_min",
       main=paste("d_min p-value =",pred_checks$Bayes_p_value["d_min"]),
       xlim = range(c(d_stats$d_pred_min,d_stats$d_min)))
  abline(v=d_stats$d_min,col="red",lwd=lwd)
  hist(d_stats$d_pred_sd,xlab="d_sd",
       main=paste("d_sd p-value =",pred_checks$Bayes_p_value["d_sd"]),
       xlim = range(c(d_stats$d_pred_sd,d_stats$d_sd)))
  abline(v=d_stats$d_sd,col="red",lwd=lwd)
  hist(d_stats$d_pred_span,xlab="d_span",
       main=paste("d_span p-value =",pred_checks$Bayes_p_value["d_span"]),
       xlim = range(c(d_stats$d_pred_span,d_stats$d_span)))
  abline(v=d_stats$d_span,col="red",lwd=lwd)
  hist(d_stats$d_pred_mean,xlab="d_mean",
       main=paste("d_mean p-value =",pred_checks$Bayes_p_value["d_mean"]),
       xlim = range(c(d_stats$d_pred_mean,d_stats$d_mean)))
  abline(v=d_stats$d_mean,col="red",lwd=lwd)
}
Y_pred_mat = as.mcmc(fit_JAGS)[[1]][, paste("Y_pred[", 1:n, "]", sep = "")]
pred_checks = compute_Bayes_p_value(Y_pred_mat, dat_linear$JAGS$Y)
pred_checks$Bayes_p_value
plot_pred_checks(pred_checks)


JAGS_Linear_pred = function() {
  # Likelihood
  for (i in 1:n) {
    Y[i]  ~ dnorm(mu[i], inv_var)
    mu[i] <- beta[1] + beta[2] * X[i]
  }
  #prediction
  for (i in 1:n_pred) {
    Y_pred[i]  ~ dnorm(mu_pred[i], inv_var)
    mu_pred[i] <- beta[1] + beta[2] * X_pred[i]
  }
  
  
  #Priors
  beta[1] ~ dnorm(0, 0.1)
  beta[2] ~ dnorm(0, 0.1)
  
  inv_var ~ dgamma(0.01, 0.01)
}
